HeatTreee Visualizations

#Begin by setting your working directory to the folder with each of your files
#setwd()

#Load your taxa table
otu <- read_csv('otu.csv')
## Warning: Missing column names filled in: 'X1' [1]
## Parsed with column specification:
## cols(
##   .default = col_double(),
##   X1 = col_character()
## )
## See spec(...) for full column specifications.
#Because our data did not have a label for the first column, we are naming it otu_id
names(otu)[1] <- 'otu_id'
##Some of our samples had a - in their file name. This can sometimes cause issues with R so we have changed the 
#sample names to no longer have the - but not have a _
names(otu) <- sapply(names(otu), function(x) gsub('-', '_', as.character(x)))

# Import metadata
hmp_samples <- read_csv('Tara_oceans_mapping_file.csv')
## Parsed with column specification:
## cols(
##   SampleID = col_character(),
##   Depth = col_character(),
##   Size_fraction = col_character(),
##   Province = col_character()
## )
#name the first column sample_id
names(hmp_samples)[1] <-'sample_id'
##Some of our samples had a - in their file name. This can sometimes cause issues with R so we have changed the 
#sample names to no longer have the - but not have a _
hmp_samples <- hmp_samples %>% mutate(sample_id = gsub('-','_', sample_id))
hmp_samples <- hmp_samples %>% group_by(Depth)
hmp_samples <- hmp_samples %>% group_by(Province, add=T)
hmp_samples <- hmp_samples %>% group_by(Size_fraction, add=T)

##Load taxonomic data file
taxa <- read_csv('taxa.csv')
## Warning: Missing column names filled in: 'X1' [1]
## Parsed with column specification:
## cols(
##   X1 = col_character(),
##   Domain = col_character(),
##   Phylum = col_character(),
##   Class = col_character(),
##   Order = col_character(),
##   Family = col_character(),
##   Genus = col_character()
## )
#taxa <- as.data.frame(taxa)
#rename the first column as otu_id
names(taxa)[1] <- 'otu_id'
#visualizae the taxa file
str(taxa)
## Classes 'spec_tbl_df', 'tbl_df', 'tbl' and 'data.frame': 35651 obs. of  7 variables:
##  $ otu_id: chr  "Seq1" "Seq2" "Seq3" "Seq4" ...
##  $ Domain: chr  "undef" "Bacteria" "Bacteria" "Bacteria" ...
##  $ Phylum: chr  "undef" "Proteobacteria" "Cyanobacteria" "Proteobacteria" ...
##  $ Class : chr  "undef" "Alphaproteobacteria" "Cyanobacteria" "Alphaproteobacteria" ...
##  $ Order : chr  "undef" "Rhodospirillales" "SubsectionI" "Rhodospirillales" ...
##  $ Family: chr  "undef" "Rhodospirillaceae" "FamilyI" "Rhodospirillaceae" ...
##  $ Genus : chr  "undef" "AEGEAN-169 marine group" "Prochlorococcus" "AEGEAN-169 marine group" ...
##  - attr(*, "spec")=
##   .. cols(
##   ..   X1 = col_character(),
##   ..   Domain = col_character(),
##   ..   Phylum = col_character(),
##   ..   Class = col_character(),
##   ..   Order = col_character(),
##   ..   Family = col_character(),
##   ..   Genus = col_character()
##   .. )
##Because the code needs the taxonomic data to be in a specific format, we are adding in additional 
#information to each of out taxonomic columns
taxa <- taxa
taxa$Domain <- paste0("k__", taxa$Domain)
taxa$Phylum <- paste0("p__", taxa$Phylum)
taxa$Class <- paste0("c__", taxa$Class)
taxa$Order <- paste0("o__", taxa$Order)
taxa$Family <- paste0("f__", taxa$Family)
taxa$Genus <- paste0("g__", taxa$Genus)

##We are merging together all of our taxonomic groups into one continuous string
taxa <- taxa %>% mutate(lineage = paste("r__Root", Domain, Phylum, Class, Order, Family, Genus, sep=";"))
#This column is called lineage
taxa <- taxa %>% select(otu_id, lineage)

#View the first bit of the OTU table to make sure the columns look correct
otu[1:5, 1:3]
## # A tibble: 5 x 3
##   otu_id TARA_018_DCM_0.22_1.6 TARA_018_SRF_0.22_1.6
##   <chr>                  <dbl>                 <dbl>
## 1 Seq1                    5101                  5314
## 2 Seq2                    1021                  1348
## 3 Seq3                    2697                  2580
## 4 Seq4                     605                   909
## 5 Seq5                    3786                  3672
##Join the otu and taxonomic files together
to_mc <- inner_join(taxa, otu)
## Joining, by = "otu_id"
#View joined files
to_mc[1:5, 1:4]
## # A tibble: 5 x 4
##   otu_id lineage                       TARA_018_DCM_0.22… TARA_018_SRF_0.2…
##   <chr>  <chr>                                      <dbl>             <dbl>
## 1 Seq1   r__Root;k__undef;p__undef;c_…               5101              5314
## 2 Seq2   r__Root;k__Bacteria;p__Prote…               1021              1348
## 3 Seq3   r__Root;k__Bacteria;p__Cyano…               2697              2580
## 4 Seq4   r__Root;k__Bacteria;p__Prote…                605               909
## 5 Seq5   r__Root;k__Bacteria;p__Cyano…               3786              3672
##Create an object that is complementary with the metacoder program. 
obj <- parse_tax_data(to_mc,
                      class_cols = "lineage", # the column that contains taxonomic information
                      class_sep = ";", # The character used to separate taxa in the classification
                      class_regex = "^(.+)__(.+)$", # Regex identifying where the data for each taxon is
                      class_key = c(tax_rank = "info", # A key describing each regex capture group
                                    tax_name = "taxon_name"))

#View this object
print(obj)
## <Taxmap>
##   3781 taxa: aab. Root, aac. undef ... fpl. Thiococcus
##   3781 edges: NA->aab, aab->aac ... bvt->fpk, bei->fpl
##   2 data sets:
##     tax_data:
##       # A tibble: 35,651 x 142
##         taxon_id otu_id lineage TARA_018_DCM_0.… TARA_018_SRF_0.…
##         <chr>    <chr>  <chr>              <dbl>            <dbl>
##       1 cgy      Seq1   r__Roo…             5101             5314
##       2 cgz      Seq2   r__Roo…             1021             1348
##       3 cha      Seq3   r__Roo…             2697             2580
##       # … with 3.565e+04 more rows, and 137 more variables:
##       #   TARA_023_DCM_0.22_1.6 <dbl>,
##       #   TARA_023_SRF_0.22_1.6 <dbl>,
##       #   TARA_025_DCM_0.22_1.6 <dbl>,
##       #   TARA_025_SRF_0.22_1.6 <dbl>,
##       #   TARA_030_DCM_0.22_1.6 <dbl>,
##       #   TARA_030_SRF_0.22_1.6 <dbl>,
##       #   TARA_031_SRF_0.22_1.6 <dbl>,
##       #   TARA_032_DCM_0.22_1.6 <dbl>,
##       #   TARA_032_SRF_0.22_1.6 <dbl>,
##       #   TARA_033_SRF_0.22_1.6 <dbl>, …
##     class_data:
##       # A tibble: 249,557 x 5
##         taxon_id input_index tax_rank tax_name regex_match
##         <chr>          <int> <chr>    <chr>    <chr>      
##       1 aab                1 r        Root     r__Root    
##       2 aac                1 k        undef    k__undef   
##       3 aaf                1 p        undef    p__undef   
##       # … with 2.496e+05 more rows
##   0 functions:
obj$data$tax_data <- zero_low_counts(obj, data = "tax_data", min_count = 5)
## No `cols` specified, so using all numeric columns:
##    TARA_018_DCM_0.22_1.6 ... TARA_099_SRF_0.22_3
## Zeroing 321593 of 4955489 counts less than 5.
no_reads <- rowSums(obj$data$tax_data[, hmp_samples$sample_id]) == 0
sum(no_reads)
## [1] 25181
obj <- filter_obs(obj, data = "tax_data", ! no_reads, drop_taxa = TRUE)
print(obj)
## <Taxmap>
##   1839 taxa: aab. Root, aac. undef ... emz. Mucilaginibacter
##   1839 edges: NA->aab, aab->aac ... bot->emr, buh->emz
##   2 data sets:
##     tax_data:
##       # A tibble: 10,470 x 140
##         taxon_id TARA_018_DCM_0.… TARA_018_SRF_0.…
##         <chr>               <dbl>            <dbl>
##       1 cgy                  5101             5314
##       2 cgz                  1021             1348
##       3 cha                  2697             2580
##       # … with 1.047e+04 more rows, and 137 more variables:
##       #   TARA_023_DCM_0.22_1.6 <dbl>,
##       #   TARA_023_SRF_0.22_1.6 <dbl>,
##       #   TARA_025_DCM_0.22_1.6 <dbl>,
##       #   TARA_025_SRF_0.22_1.6 <dbl>,
##       #   TARA_030_DCM_0.22_1.6 <dbl>,
##       #   TARA_030_SRF_0.22_1.6 <dbl>,
##       #   TARA_031_SRF_0.22_1.6 <dbl>,
##       #   TARA_032_DCM_0.22_1.6 <dbl>,
##       #   TARA_032_SRF_0.22_1.6 <dbl>,
##       #   TARA_033_SRF_0.22_1.6 <dbl>, …
##     class_data:
##       # A tibble: 241,076 x 5
##         taxon_id input_index tax_rank tax_name regex_match
##         <chr>          <int> <chr>    <chr>    <chr>      
##       1 aab                1 r        Root     r__Root    
##       2 aac                1 k        undef    k__undef   
##       3 aaf                1 p        undef    p__undef   
##       # … with 2.411e+05 more rows
##   0 functions:
obj$data$tax_data <- calc_obs_props(obj, "tax_data")
## No `cols` specified, so using all numeric columns:
##    TARA_018_DCM_0.22_1.6 ... TARA_099_SRF_0.22_3
## Calculating proportions from counts for 139 columns for 10470 observations.
obj$data$tax_abund <- calc_taxon_abund(obj, "tax_data",cols = hmp_samples$sample_id)
## Summing per-taxon counts from 139 columns for 1839 taxa
obj$data$tax_occ <- calc_n_samples(obj, "tax_abund", groups = hmp_samples$Depth)
## NOTE: Using the "groups" option without the "cols" option can yeild incorrect results if the column order is different from the group order.
## No `cols` specified, so using all numeric columns:
##    TARA_018_DCM_0.22_1.6 ... TARA_099_SRF_0.22_3
## Calculating number of samples with a value greater than 0 for 139 columns in 4 groups for 1839 observations
set.seed(1) # This makes the plot appear the same each time it is run 
heat_tree(obj, 
          node_label = taxon_names,
          node_size = n_obs,
          node_color = DCM, #This is where you determine which factor you want to display
          node_size_axis_label = "OTU count",
           node_label_size_range = c(0.02, 0.02),
          node_label_max = 50,
          node_color_axis_label = "Samples with reads",
          layout = "davidson-harel", # The primary layout algorithm
          initial_layout = "reingold-tilford") # The layout algorithm that initializes node locations

obj$data$diff_table$wilcox_p_value <- p.adjust(obj$data$diff_table$wilcox_p_value, method = "fdr")
range(obj$data$diff_table$wilcox_p_value, finite = TRUE)
## Warning in min(x): no non-missing arguments to min; returning Inf
## Warning in max(x): no non-missing arguments to max; returning -Inf
## [1]  Inf -Inf
obj$data$diff_table$log2_median_ratio[obj$data$diff_table$wilcox_p_value > 0.05] <- 0
obj$data$diff_table <- compare_groups(obj, dataset = "tax_abund",
                                      cols = hmp_samples$sample_id, # What columns of sample data to use
                                      groups = hmp_samples$Depth) # What category each sample is assigned to
